The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                      
	 New Delhi, Sept. 30: Income tax at source will be deducted only on 40 per cent of the salary arrears given to central government employees in the current fiscal following the implementation of the Sixth Pay Commissions recommendations. The government has decided to pay 40 per cent of the arrears to its employees this fiscal and 60 percent in the next fiscal.					            
	 New Delhi, Sept. 30: SAIL is collaborating with Larsen amp; Toubro for setting up a 1,600MW power plant to meet its future energy requirements. According to the MoU signed today, the power plant will be developed, managed and owned by the two companies.                    
	 New Delhi, Sept. 30: To put brake on the sluggish pace of excise duty collections, the government has introduced a system of gathering information through third parties on evasion of payment.                    
	 Mumbai, Sept. 30: Ashok Leyland has entered into a joint venture with US-based agricultural equipment maker John Deere for the manufacturing and marketing of construction equipment.                    
	 Mumbai, Sept. 30: Bombay High Court has adjourned the hearing of the gas supply dispute case between Reliance Industries Ltd and Reliance Natural Resources Ltd till October 6.                                                                                                                       
